Tolkien spent four decades &quot;creating&quot; a detailed world, including languages, geography, myths and ancient history, so you will never find a fantasy book with an atmosphere that can be compared to Middle Earth. Most of this work wasn't mean to be released, it was only for his own use and enjoyment, and as a background for the books. Middle Earth is &quot;alive&quot; and almost &quot;real&quot;. Given a writer with the same talent, he would need the same unbeleivable effort and dedication to produce a similar work. The current market would never allow a succesful writer to release a couple books in 30 years, he would be pressed to release every year and make a profit with his first book, and this would probably affect negatively his work.<br>
<br>
